Delicious Northern Thai food! The khao soi was amazing with noodles cooked perfectly al dente and a rich, flavorful broth. Loved their creative dessert too ‚Äî mango ice cream with a sweet and salty sauce, super refreshing and unique.

My Khao Soi Quest continues! Banthat Thong has it's fair share of both Isan and Lanna cuisine and you'll be spoilt for choice. This clean-cut nondescript little cafe' style restaurant is just one of many that my Thai ex-colleague recommended. As usual, my eyes were bigger than my stomach and I over ordered. I just had to try it all. Ordered both the chicken & pork belly Khao Soi. The coconut curry base gravy was the same as far as I could tell, and both had the flat egg noodles cooked slightly al dente. The 'authentic' version as purist would have it would include crispy deep fried egg noodles. This was accompanied by crispy fried wonton skins instead. Honestly, I'm not particular as long as it tastes good, I'm not ideological when it comes to food. The Khantoke dish of pork crackling, northern style sausage and fried pork with nam prik num green chili was a greedy afterthought, and it was pretty decent. Service was promp/attentive and price point was normal Bkk cafe. In the interest of accuracy, this is a solid 4.4 stars
